<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Build Tree API</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css" />
    <style>
      body {
        background: radial-gradient(circle at top, rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.08), transparent 55%),
          #f8fafc;
      }

      main {
        text-align: center;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 2.5rem;
      }

      header {
        display: grid;
        gap: 1rem;
      }

      header p {
        max-width: 640px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        color: #475569;
      }

      .cta-group {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        justify-content: center;
        gap: 1rem;
      }

      .cta-group a {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 0.9rem 1.85rem;
        border-radius: 999px;
        text-decoration: none;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: #ffffff;
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2563eb, #7c3aed);
        transition: transform 0.18s ease, box-shadow 0.18s ease;
      }

      .cta-group a.secondary {
        background: none;
        color: #2563eb;
        border: 1px solid rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.4);
        backdrop-filter: blur(6px);
      }

      .cta-group a:hover {
        transform: translateY(-2px);
        box-shadow: 0 12px 25px rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.25);
      }

      .info-grid {
        display: grid;
        gap: 1.5rem;
        text-align: left;
      }

      .info-grid section {
        background: #ffffff;
        border-radius: 16px;
        padding: 1.75rem;
        box-shadow: 0 18px 40px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.08);
      }

      .info-grid h2 {
        margin-top: 0;
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      }

      .info-grid .docs-list {
        display: grid;
        gap: 0.75rem;
      }

      .info-grid .docs-list a {
        display: block;
        padding: 0.9rem 1.1rem;
        border-radius: 14px;
        border: 1px solid rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.12);
        text-decoration: none;
        color: #1e293b;
        background: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.02);
        transition: border-color 0.15s ease, transform 0.15s ease;
      }

      .info-grid .docs-list a:hover {
        border-color: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.45);
        transform: translateY(-1px);
      }

      .info-grid ul {
        margin: 0;
        padding-left: 1.25rem;
        color: #475569;
      }

      .info-grid code {
        font-family: 'Fira Code', Consolas, 'Courier New', monospace;
        padding: 0.1rem 0.35rem;
        background: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.2);
        border-radius: 0.35rem;
      }

      @media (min-width: 900px) {
        .info-grid {
          grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <header>
        <h1>Build Tree API</h1>
        <p>
          Turn indented outlines into a structured tree with rich validation feedback. Explore the playground,
          inspect our OpenAPI docs, or embed the utility in your own workflow.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="cta-group">
        <a href="<%= playgroundUrl %>">Launch Playground</a>
        <a class="secondary" href="/docs/swagger">Swagger UI</a>
        <a class="secondary" href="/docs/redoc">Redoc</a>
      </div>

      <div class="info-grid">
        <section>
          <h2>Quick Start</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>POST indented text to <code>/api/build-tree</code> and receive structured JSON output.</li>
            <li>Reuse the same logic inline via the playground form for rapid experimentation.</li>
            <li>Validation guards against empty input, inconsistent indentation, and malformed outlines.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Documentation</h2>
          <p>Pick your preferred format to explore the service contract.</p>
          <div class="docs-list">
            <% docs.forEach(doc => { %>
              <a href="<%= doc.href %>"><%= doc.name %> &rarr;</a>
            <% }) %>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Feature Highlights</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Hierarchical output preserves indentation depth as <code>level</code> metadata.</li>
            <li>Simple error model with explicit <code>errorCode</code> and human-readable messages.</li>
            <li>Shared utility layer with the unit-testing playground ensures parity between environments.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Integration Tips</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Normalize input to spaces or tabs consistently before posting for predictable levels.</li>
            <li>Wrap API calls in your own CLI or editor extension to preview outlines on the fly.</li>
            <li>Combine with your favourite test runner to enforce indentation rules in lint pipelines.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>

